cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it deals with the task of text-image retrieval. It may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as it proposes a novel approach for cross-modal interaction and feature fusion, and introduces a new loss function for training.
